global_investment_restrictions.value: max 50% below investment grade debt securities; max 20% unrated debt securities; max 20% perpetual debt securities; max 10% distressed debt securities; max 20% onshore PRC securities; max 10% Equity Linked Notes; max 10% Credit Linked Notes; max 10% REITs; max 20% MBS/ABS; max 5% contingent convertible bonds
global_investment_restrictions.source_quote: The Sub-Fund may invest up to 50% of its assets in below investment grade debt securities, 20% of its assets each in unrated debt securities and perpetual debt securities. The Sub-Fund will not invest in distressed debt securities (at the time of purchase). However, the Sub-Fund may temporarily hold up to 10% in distressed debt securities as a result of credit downgrades. The Sub-Fund may invest up to 20% of its assets in onshore PRC securities... The Sub-Fund may invest up to 10% of its assets each in Equity Linked Notes, Credit Linked Notes and REITs.
global_investment_restrictions.rationale: Found in the Policies section detailing specific investment limits.

global_investment_restrictions.value: At least 67% of assets invested in equities and debt securities issued or guaranteed by governments or agencies, globally; The Sub-Fund may invest in below investment grade and unrated debt securities; however, debt securities will typically have an average credit quality of investment grade; The Sub-Fund will hold between 30% and 70% of assets in equities, and between 30% and 70% of assets in debt securities; At least 51% of assets are invested in issuers with positive environmental and/or social characteristics; The Sub-Fund invests at least 10% of assets in Sustainable Investments.

global_investment_restrictions.value: max 20% below investment grade debt securities; max 20% unrated debt securities; max 20% perpetual debt securities; max 10% distressed debt securities; max 45% Equity Linked Notes; max 10% Credit Linked Notes; max 25% REITs; max 20% MBS/ABS; at least 67% in US income generating securities
global_investment_restrictions.source_quote: The Sub-Fund may invest up to 20% of its assets each in below investment grade debt securities, unrated debt securities and perpetual debt securities. The Sub-Fund will not invest in distressed debt securities (at the time of purchase). However, the Sub-Fund may temporarily hold up to 10% in distressed debt securities as a result of credit downgrades. The Sub-Fund may invest up to 45% of its assets in Equity Linked Notes and up to 10% of its assets in Credit Linked Notes. The Sub-Fund may invest up to 25% of its assets in REITs. The Sub-Fund is expected to invest up to 20% of its assets in MBS/ABS of any credit quality.

observations: The document provides a comprehensive overview of various sub-funds, each with specific objectives, investment processes, and risk profiles.
The fee tables are specific to each fund and provide detailed information on charges and expenses.
Cross-references to external documents like KIIDs indicate that some information is not contained within the prospectus itself.
All fund names mentioned by the explorer are present in the source document but are prefixed with 'JPMorgan Investment Funds - ' which was not included in the explorer's findings.
Pages 61-63 contain detailed tables on investment restrictions and diversification requirements, which are crucial for fund managers to understand the limits on investments.
Pages 69-70 provide a comprehensive table on derivatives usage across various sub-funds, indicating expected leverage and types of derivatives used.
Pages 71-73 focus on ESG integration and sustainable investing approaches, highlighting the importance of ESG factors in investment decisions.
Page 75 provides pre-contractual disclosure for the Europe Select Equity Fund, detailing its sustainable investment objectives and criteria.
Page 80 includes a table on EU Taxonomy alignment, which is important for understanding the fund's compliance with environmental regulations.
The fund names in the explorer findings do not match the exact capitalization and formatting in the source document.
Pages 241-244 discuss various operational and legal rights related to fund management, including suspension of dealing, liquidation, and merger processes.
Pages 245-246 provide detailed information on pricing, valuation, and execution policies, including swing pricing and best execution practices.
Pages 251-254 contain detailed information about the fund's business operations, structure, and service providers, including the management company, depositary, and auditors.
The explorer used an en dash (–) instead of a hyphen (-) in the names 'JPMorgan Investment Funds – Europe Select Equity Fund' and 'JPMorgan Investment Funds – Global Select Equity Fund'.

The page contains contact information for JPMorgan Asset Management, including email, website, and physical address. It also notes that the information is not for use by or distribution to US persons.
